## 1. Canonical Source

The **single source of truth** for the Consensus Dev Agent version is:

```
VERSION
```

This is a plain-text file at the repository root. It contains exactly one line: a valid [Semantic Versioning 2.0.0](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html) string with **no `v` prefix**, **no trailing whitespace**, and **no trailing newline beyond the final line**.

Example content:

```
0.1.0
```

All other version representations in the repository are **derived** from this file. If any derived target diverges from the `VERSION` file, the build is broken and must fail closed.

---

## 2. Propagation Targets

The canonical version in `VERSION` must be propagated to exactly four targets. Each target has a defined binding location and format.

| # | Target | File | Field / Key | Format | Example |
|---|--------|------|-------------|--------|---------|
| 1 | **Swift shell** | `Forge/Info.plist` | `CFBundleShortVersionString` | Raw SemVer string (no prefix) | `0.1.0` |
| 2 | **Python backend** | `forge_agent/version.py` | `AGENT_VERSION` | Python string literal | `AGENT_VERSION = "0.1.0"` |
| 3 | **Python packaging** | `pyproject.toml` | `version` | TOML string value | `version = "0.1.0"` |
| 4 | **Git release tag** | Git ref | Tag name | `v` prefix + SemVer | `v0.1.0` |

### 2.1 Binding Rules

- **Info.plist (`CFBundleShortVersionString`):** Must be the exact string from `VERSION`. No `v` prefix. No build metadata suffix. `CFBundleVersion` (build number) is managed separately and is not governed by this contract.
- **version.py (`AGENT_VERSION`):** Must be a module-level string constant whose value is identical to the content of `VERSION`. This constant is read at runtime during the IPC handshake.
- **pyproject.toml (`version`):** Must match `VERSION` exactly. This is the version reported by Python packaging tools (`pip show`, `importlib.metadata`).
- **Git tag:** Created only at release time. Format is `v{VERSION}` (e.g., `v0.1.0`). The `v` prefix exists **only** on git tags, nowhere else.

### 2.2 Propagation Target Hierarchy

```
VERSION  (canonical, plain text, repository root)
  ├── Forge/Info.plist            → CFBundleShortVersionString
  ├── forge_agent/version.py      → AGENT_VERSION
  ├── pyproject.toml              → version
  └── git tag                     → v{VERSION}
```

All arrows are **one-directional**. No derived target ever writes back to `VERSION`. The `VERSION` file is the root of the dependency graph.

