## 8. Compatibility Matrix

This matrix defines which version combinations are considered compatible across the Swift shell and Python backend processes.

| Swift Shell Version | Python Backend Version | Compatible? | Behavior |
|--------------------|-----------------------|-------------|----------|
| `X.Y.Z` | `X.Y.Z` | **Yes** | Handshake succeeds, normal operation |
| `X.Y.Z` | `X.Y.W` (W ≠ Z) | **No** | Handshake fails closed, connection refused |
| `X.Y.Z` | `X.A.B` (A ≠ Y) | **No** | Handshake fails closed, connection refused |
| `X.Y.Z` | `A.B.C` (A ≠ X) | **No** | Handshake fails closed, connection refused |
| `X.Y.Z` | `X.Y.Z-alpha.1` | **No** | Handshake fails closed, connection refused |
| `X.Y.Z-alpha.1` | `X.Y.Z-alpha.1` | **Yes** | Handshake succeeds, normal operation |
| `X.Y.Z-alpha.1` | `X.Y.Z-alpha.2` | **No** | Handshake fails closed, connection refused |

**Rule:** Compatibility is determined by **exact string equality** of the version field. There are no version ranges, no "compatible with" semantics, and no negotiation. This is intentional -- it eliminates an entire class of subtle incompatibility bugs at the cost of requiring coordinated deployments.

